But Berlin no longer needs Paris as a means of gaining political legitimacy, and has already imposed its own economic policy on Europe, leaving France’s devastated economy in distress.
The result is a right-wing anti-EU party, Marín Le Pen, the National Front, which has just won decisive additional elections, putting the ruling party of socialists in third place.
Front is now the most popular party in France with 24 per cent of votes — a timely warning to British Labourers that it cannot be assumed that splits among the right will automatically affect the left.
